<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-03-22T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-03-22T09:00:00-05:00" n="249" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d249">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">862.20/767: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Poland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Cudahy</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Warsaw</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-22T15:00:00+01:00">March 22, 1935—3
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 4:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>23. Please refer to last sentence my telegram number 20.<note n="56" xml:id="d249fn56">March 18, 8 p.m., not printed.</note> Beck
                                advises that tomorrow Polish Ambassador in Berlin will verbally make
                                a statement to the German Government directing attention to
                                consequences involved in the violation of Versailles Treaty by the
                                evils of conscription. This announcement will be orally and
                                informally and will be more mild and conciliatory in tone than that
                                which will be given to press.</p>
                            <p>Foregoing repeated to Berlin.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cudahy</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>